## Copies

Don't forget that `python` *does not make copies unless told to do so* (same as with any mutable type)

If you are not careful enough, this typically leads to a *lot of errors* and to being fired !!

::: {#5e368e8d .cell ExecuteTime='{"end_time":"2022-01-19T10:23:51.294522Z","start_time":"2022-01-19T10:23:51.288358Z"}' slideshow='{"slide_type":"-"}' execution_count=71}
``` {.python .cell-code}
y = x = np.arange(6)
x[2] = 123
y
```
:::


::: {#827483b5 .cell ExecuteTime='{"end_time":"2022-01-19T10:24:34.145203Z","start_time":"2022-01-19T10:24:34.140801Z"}' execution_count=72}
``` {.python .cell-code}
x is y
```
:::


::: {#9aeadd06 .cell ExecuteTime='{"end_time":"2022-01-19T10:24:38.815817Z","start_time":"2022-01-19T10:24:38.811878Z"}' slideshow='{"slide_type":"subslide"}' execution_count=73}
``` {.python .cell-code}
# A real copy
y = x.copy()
x is y 
```
:::


::: {#fa6cb006 .cell ExecuteTime='{"end_time":"2022-01-19T10:24:57.551439Z","start_time":"2022-01-19T10:24:57.548073Z"}' execution_count=74}
``` {.python .cell-code}
# Or equivalently (but the one above is better...)
y = np.copy(x)
```
:::


::: {#000ea959 .cell ExecuteTime='{"end_time":"2022-01-19T10:24:57.733643Z","start_time":"2022-01-19T10:24:57.727390Z"}' execution_count=75}
